WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
- Synced and corrected by <font color="#009BCB"><b>chamallow</b></font> -
- www.addic7ed.com -

2
00:00:05.489 --> 00:00:07.174
In the criminal justice system.

3
00:00:07.241 --> 00:00:08.609
the people are represented

4
00:00:08.642 --> 00:00:11.036
by two separate. yet
equally important groups:

5
00:00:11.103 --> 00:00:12.871
the police. who investigate crime.

6
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:15.774
and the district attorneys.
who prosecute the offenders.

7
00:00:15.808 --> 00:00:19.286
These are their stories.

8
00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:22.106
Ooh.

9
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:32.624
I know. buddy. I know it's cold.

10
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:40.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

11
00:00:55.089 --> 00:00:56.690
Hello?

12
00:01:13.507 --> 00:01:16.502
Oh. plenty of room at the end.

13
00:01:34.211 --> 00:01:35.512
Banjo?

14
00:01:39.892 --> 00:01:41.034
What is it. boy?

15
00:01:48.609 --> 00:01:49.827
Ugh.

16
00:02:55.943 --> 00:02:58.212
Vagrant flagged down a
squad car up the block.

17
00:02:58.278 --> 00:03:01.081
Dude was freaked. Said
his dog had found a body.

18
00:03:01.148 --> 00:03:03.217
The little fella's pretty cute.

19
00:03:03.283 --> 00:03:05.477
The dog or the vagrant?

20
00:03:05.544 --> 00:03:06.544
Each of these storage spaces

21
00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:10.190
belong to one of the condos upstairs.

22
00:03:10.257 --> 00:03:12.459
Ooh. damn. Whew.

23
00:03:12.493 --> 00:03:14.094
Yeah. it's pretty ripe.
You're gonna want this.

24
00:03:14.161 --> 00:03:15.696
Helps hide the smell.

25
00:03:15.796 --> 00:03:17.431
Yeah. I'm good with that. though.

26
00:03:17.564 --> 00:03:19.533
I'm good too.

27
00:03:19.633 --> 00:03:21.101
Lock was clipped.

28
00:03:21.134 --> 00:03:25.472
The door to the exterior
was pried open too.

29
00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:26.940
Ew. All right.

30
00:03:27.007 --> 00:03:29.309
Female. from the looks of it.

31
00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:32.004
Not a very tall one if she
could fit inside this suitcase.

32
00:03:32.070 --> 00:03:33.639
No. definitely on the shorter side.

33
00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:35.299
Um. didn't find any ID.

34
00:03:35.332 --> 00:03:37.651
and based on decomposition and
the amount of accumulated dust.

35
00:03:37.718 --> 00:03:39.912
I'd say she's been
down here a long time.

36
00:03:40.012 --> 00:03:41.989
Like months. not weeks.

37
00:03:42.022 --> 00:03:43.857
Jesus. somebody just
left her down here to rot?

38
00:03:43.924 --> 00:03:45.317
I can't take this no more. man.

39
00:03:45.350 --> 00:03:46.760
Give me the smell
stuff. I changed my mind.

40
00:03:46.827 --> 00:03:49.947
Thank you.

41
00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:55.168
We need to talk to
whoever owns the apartment

42
00:03:55.202 --> 00:03:56.970
the storage unit 9F belongs to.

43
00:03:57.004 --> 00:03:59.031
Uh. it's going to be tricky.

44
00:03:59.097 --> 00:04:01.808
9F is owned by a man named Zhang Tao.

45
00:04:01.875 --> 00:04:03.176
Why is that tricky?

46
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:04.978
Well. he owns the unit.
but he doesn't live in it.

47
00:04:05.012 --> 00:04:08.582
His referral address is in Shanghai.

48
00:04:08.682 --> 00:04:10.918
As far as I know. he's never
even set foot in the place.

49
00:04:10.984 --> 00:04:12.719
So the owner rents it out?

50
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:15.389
No. it's just sitting there unoccupied.

51
00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:17.724
It's true for most of the units.

52
00:04:17.791 --> 00:04:19.927
Rich dudes from other
countries bought them all up.

53
00:04:19.993 --> 00:04:21.194
You telling me this giant.

54
00:04:21.228 --> 00:04:22.621
brand-new building is basically empty?

55
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:23.722
I guess it's a good investment

56
00:04:23.789 --> 00:04:26.400
or tax shelter or... I don't know.

57
00:04:26.466 --> 00:04:27.601
Must be a smart money move somehow.

58
00:04:27.668 --> 00:04:29.227
'cause they're all doing it.

59
00:04:29.294 --> 00:04:32.105
Ah. housing crisis brought to
you by conspicuous consumption.

60
00:04:32.205 --> 00:04:34.641
So who would have access to
the basement storage units?

61
00:04:34.708 --> 00:04:37.110
Well. w-we've currently
got about 27 residents

62
00:04:37.210 --> 00:04:40.113
actually living in the units.
so any of them. obviously.

63
00:04:40.213 --> 00:04:43.909
But honestly... Could have been anyone.

64
00:04:43.976 --> 00:04:45.085
Narrows it down.

65
00:04:45.185 --> 00:04:46.645
Yeah. word spread
around the neighborhood

66
00:04:46.712 --> 00:04:48.021
about the building being empty.

67
00:04:48.155 --> 00:04:49.823
so people keep breaking
into the basement.

68
00:04:49.890 --> 00:04:51.124
Got any cameras down there?

69
00:04:51.191 --> 00:04:52.693
Yeah. of course. I can
get you the footage.

70
00:04:52.726 --> 00:04:53.726
Yeah. we'll need everything you got

71
00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:55.028
for the last few months.

72
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:58.198
System only stores the
data for a couple weeks.

73
00:04:58.265 --> 00:05:00.600
Sorry. guys.

74
00:05:05.906 --> 00:05:07.608
The body was in rough shape.

75
00:05:07.674 --> 00:05:11.178
She'd been in that suitcase for
four or five months at least.

76
00:05:11.244 --> 00:05:13.839
Cause of death appears
to be a cervical fracture

77
00:05:13.939 --> 00:05:15.983
between the C1 and C2 vertebrae.

78
00:05:16.083 --> 00:05:18.176
- Somebody snapped her neck.
- Mm-hmm.

79
00:05:18.243 --> 00:05:19.411
Based on everything I'm seeing.

80
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:21.221
I'm comfortable ruling this a homicide.

81
00:05:21.355 --> 00:05:22.614
Were you able to ID her?

82
00:05:22.681 --> 00:05:24.391
The skin on her fingers
was too decomposed

83
00:05:24.458 --> 00:05:25.951
to get a clean print.

84
00:05:26.018 --> 00:05:28.295
I ran her DNA through
the system. but no luck.

85
00:05:28.362 --> 00:05:29.563
What can you tell us about her?

86
00:05:29.596 --> 00:05:31.590
She was Caucasian.

87
00:05:31.623 --> 00:05:33.500
Analysis of the pubic symphysis.

88
00:05:33.567 --> 00:05:35.293
cranial sutures. and sternal ribbons

89
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:38.572
tells me she was
post-puberty. but not by much.

90
00:05:38.605 --> 00:05:40.741
Likely in her late teens or early 20s.

91
00:05:40.774 --> 00:05:42.075
Any distinct characteristics

92
00:05:42.142 --> 00:05:44.302
that might make her easier to identify?

93
00:05:44.369 --> 00:05:47.180
She did have a tattoo
on her left forearm.

94
00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:48.315
The fluorescence spectrometer

95
00:05:48.382 --> 00:05:49.683
was able to pick up the pigment.

96
00:05:49.750 --> 00:05:51.768
You can just make out the letters.

97
00:05:55.389 --> 00:05:58.158
Confirmed with the Chinese
embassy that Zhang Tao.

98
00:05:58.258 --> 00:06:00.460
the owner of the storage
unit where the body was found.

99
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:02.821
has never actually traveled
to the United States.

100
00:06:02.888 --> 00:06:04.464
And similar to the
building security system.

101
00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:07.834
the street cams in the area
only store data for two months.

102
00:06:07.934 --> 00:06:09.795
There's no footage from
around the time of the murder.

103
00:06:09.828 --> 00:06:11.171
What about forensics?

104
00:06:11.238 --> 00:06:13.957
Well. the techs were able to pull
a partial print off the suitcase.

105
00:06:13.990 --> 00:06:15.542
Okay. wonderful. Actual evidence.

106
00:06:15.609 --> 00:06:17.144
But no hits in the system.

107
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:19.571
There's always a chance that
the print belongs to our vic.

108
00:06:19.638 --> 00:06:21.448
Significantly less wonderful.

109
00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:24.017
Okay. so we don't
know who our victim is.

110
00:06:24.084 --> 00:06:26.586
we have no suspects.
and we have no leads.

111
00:06:26.686 --> 00:06:28.355
It's a tough one. Lou.

112
00:06:28.422 --> 00:06:30.557
Start with identifying our vic.

113
00:06:30.624 --> 00:06:32.017
A young girl missing for that long?

114
00:06:32.084 --> 00:06:33.819
Somebody must have noticed.

115
00:06:35.262 --> 00:06:38.398
We get about 13.000 missing
person reports annually.

116
00:06:38.465 --> 00:06:40.525
And that's just for New York City.

117
00:06:40.592 --> 00:06:42.819
Statewide. the number is way higher.

118
00:06:42.853 --> 00:06:45.931
The majority are between
15 and 25 years old.

119
00:06:45.997 --> 00:06:47.574
Same age as our vic.

120
00:06:47.674 --> 00:06:49.576
So we're looking for
a needle in a haystack.

121
00:06:49.676 --> 00:06:51.169
It might not be that bleak.

122
00:06:51.203 --> 00:06:52.679
Most cases are resolved quickly.

123
00:06:52.713 --> 00:06:55.515
and it's common for one person
to rack up multiple reports.

124
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:57.084
And you get a lot of repeat customers?

125
00:06:57.184 --> 00:06:59.377
Kids run away from home. get found.

126
00:06:59.444 --> 00:07:01.421
returned. then do it again.

127
00:07:01.488 --> 00:07:05.559
It's hard to stay disappeared.
given today's technology.

128
00:07:05.625 --> 00:07:06.927
The number of current open cases

129
00:07:07.027 --> 00:07:08.862
is much smaller. only a couple hundred.

130
00:07:08.895 --> 00:07:11.848
Is it possible to search based
on what we know about our vic?

131
00:07:11.882 --> 00:07:13.133
The reports are all streamlined

132
00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:14.601
into a database we can filter.

133
00:07:14.668 --> 00:07:17.337
You said she was in
her teens or early 20s?

134
00:07:17.370 --> 00:07:18.572
Correct.

135
00:07:18.672 --> 00:07:20.674
White with black hair
and a tattoo on her arm.

136
00:07:20.707 --> 00:07:22.067
Right arm or left?

137
00:07:22.134 --> 00:07:24.035
Left.

138
00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:25.178
Eight hits.

139
00:07:25.212 --> 00:07:26.571
Do you know what the tattoo was of?

140
00:07:26.638 --> 00:07:28.782
The letters MCF.

141
00:07:28.882 --> 00:07:32.144
That one's a flower.
That one's a butterfly.

142
00:07:32.210 --> 00:07:34.354
Zodiac sign.

143
00:07:34.488 --> 00:07:35.589
No dice.

144
00:07:35.655 --> 00:07:36.790
You said a lot of missing persons

145
00:07:36.857 --> 00:07:38.191
are reported multiple times.

146
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:40.026
Is there any way to run the same search

147
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:41.895
but on closed cases?

148
00:07:41.896 --> 00:07:42.896
Worth a shot.

149
00:07:44.998 --> 00:07:46.967
Got her.

150
00:07:47.033 --> 00:07:51.897
Lucia Falasco. 18. former
gymnastics phenom from Queens.

151
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:53.265
Her birthday was last month.

152
00:07:53.331 --> 00:07:55.375
so she was 17 when she was murdered.

153
00:07:55.408 --> 00:07:57.043
Ran away from home twice last year.

154
00:07:57.110 --> 00:07:58.478
Who filed the reports?

155
00:07:58.578 --> 00:08:00.180
Guy named Craig Valparaiso.

156
00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:02.516
Yeah. he was Lucia's gymnastics coach.

157
00:08:02.616 --> 00:08:04.117
And according to state records.

158
00:08:04.184 --> 00:08:06.720
Valparaiso took full custody
of her when her mother.

159
00:08:06.753 --> 00:08:09.456
Maureen Claire Falasco.
died three years ago.

160
00:08:10.857 --> 00:08:12.409
Sounds like Lucia was trying pretty hard

161
00:08:12.442 --> 00:08:13.994
to get away from this guy.

162
00:08:14.094 --> 00:08:15.195
Been missing for over five months.

163
00:08:15.295 --> 00:08:17.063
He didn't call it in this time.

164
00:08:17.197 --> 00:08:18.265
Find out why.

165
00:08:22.102 --> 00:08:26.531
Stay focused. stay focused.

166
00:08:26.598 --> 00:08:28.425
Tighten up your form.

167
00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:30.143
You're losing it.

168
00:08:31.778 --> 00:08:33.213
You think that was acceptable?

169
00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:35.615
You think that's how you win?

170
00:08:35.649 --> 00:08:37.918
Think we can ease up
there a little bit. chief.

171
00:08:37.951 --> 00:08:39.186
What do you want?

172
00:08:39.286 --> 00:08:42.714
We'd like to talk to
you about Lucia Falasco.

173
00:08:42.781 --> 00:08:44.090
I'm not interested.

174
00:08:44.124 --> 00:08:47.219
Let's do it again. and
this time. actually try.

175
00:08:47.319 --> 00:08:49.296
I'm sorry. we said "we'd
like to talk to you"

176
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:51.264
as if you had a choice.

177
00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:53.834
We're Homicide
detectives. Lucia is dead.

178
00:08:55.727 --> 00:08:57.437
What?

179
00:08:57.504 --> 00:09:00.373
So why don't we go
downtown? We can chat there.

180
00:09:09.133 --> 00:09:11.076
I swear I didn't kill Lucia.

181
00:09:11.176 --> 00:09:12.744
I could never...

182
00:09:12.811 --> 00:09:15.580
You what? You what?

183
00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:16.680
Cared about her?

184
00:09:16.681 --> 00:09:17.891
Because from what I hear.

185
00:09:17.991 --> 00:09:19.326
you didn't seem too concerned

186
00:09:19.359 --> 00:09:21.661
when two cops showed up
and mentioned her name.

187
00:09:21.695 --> 00:09:24.689
I thought they were gonna
say she got into some trouble.

188
00:09:24.756 --> 00:09:26.733
that she needed help
with bail or something.

189
00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:27.901
I didn't know she was dead!

190
00:09:27.968 --> 00:09:29.527
If you didn't know she was dead.

191
00:09:29.594 --> 00:09:31.321
why didn't you report her missing?

192
00:09:31.354 --> 00:09:33.006
You're her legal guardian.

193
00:09:33.039 --> 00:09:34.875
She'd been gone at least five months.

194
00:09:34.941 --> 00:09:37.644
Because I'd already been
through that circus twice.

195
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.246
She just... she didn't
want to be with me.

196
00:09:39.312 --> 00:09:41.381
She kept running away. so...

197
00:09:41.481 --> 00:09:43.016
and she took off again
about six months ago.

198
00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:44.083
I just figured...

199
00:09:44.117 --> 00:09:45.318
Figured what?

200
00:09:45.452 --> 00:09:47.988
You'd let her fend for herself?

201
00:09:48.021 --> 00:09:50.023
She was going to be 18 soon.

202
00:09:50.056 --> 00:09:52.684
and then she could do
whatever she wanted anyway.

203
00:09:52.717 --> 00:09:56.329
What were you doing that made
her want to leave so badly?

204
00:09:56.363 --> 00:09:59.132
I know what you're implying.

205
00:09:59.199 --> 00:10:01.501
There was nothing like that going on.

206
00:10:01.534 --> 00:10:03.270
I never touched her.

207
00:10:03.370 --> 00:10:07.340
Not in anger. not in any way.

208
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:10.110
Well. it's very unusual

209
00:10:10.210 --> 00:10:12.537
for a gymnast's coach
to end up her guardian.

210
00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:16.016
I started coaching
her when she was nine.

211
00:10:16.049 --> 00:10:17.684
When her mom died. no
other family stepped up.

212
00:10:17.817 --> 00:10:18.977
so I took her in.

213
00:10:19.044 --> 00:10:21.288
Hmm. Quite the hero.

214
00:10:21.388 --> 00:10:23.857
It's certainly not what I planned.

215
00:10:23.924 --> 00:10:26.126
And she was talented.

216
00:10:26.226 --> 00:10:27.294
But by the time she took off.

217
00:10:27.394 --> 00:10:29.229
I... I wasn't even coaching her anymore.

218
00:10:29.262 --> 00:10:30.822
Well. what happened?

219
00:10:30.922 --> 00:10:32.098
Did you guys have a falling out?

220
00:10:32.198 --> 00:10:34.034
Two years ago. she
slipped on the uneven bars

221
00:10:34.167 --> 00:10:36.536
and ripped her shoulder
out of the socket.

222
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:38.238
Tore her labrum.

223
00:10:38.271 --> 00:10:41.207
Her career was over before it started.

224
00:10:41.308 --> 00:10:44.010
Fate's cruel little joke.

225
00:10:44.077 --> 00:10:46.104
She was messed up after that.

226
00:10:46.171 --> 00:10:47.414
Hanging out with the wrong people.

227
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:48.915
partying. staying out all night.

228
00:10:48.949 --> 00:10:50.684
I-I tried to rein her in.
but she wouldn't listen

229
00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:54.120
- to me...
- That piss you off?

230
00:10:54.187 --> 00:10:56.740
That she wasn't
respecting your authority?

231
00:10:56.773 --> 00:10:58.325
I'm telling you

232
00:10:58.425 --> 00:11:01.419
I had nothing to do with
what happened to her.

233
00:11:03.897 --> 00:11:06.266
Talk to her friend Julissa.

234
00:11:06.299 --> 00:11:07.534
First few times Lucia ran away.

235
00:11:07.634 --> 00:11:10.870
that's who they found her staying with.

236
00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:12.597
Guarantee you she knows more than I do.

237
00:11:15.133 --> 00:11:17.077
You two were close?

238
00:11:17.210 --> 00:11:19.245
Kinda. I guess.

239
00:11:19.279 --> 00:11:21.581
I hadn't known her long.
but she was a good kid.

240
00:11:21.614 --> 00:11:23.083
Just a little lost.

241
00:11:23.216 --> 00:11:25.752
She crashed with you a few
times after she ran away

242
00:11:25.785 --> 00:11:27.187
from her coach's house. yeah?

243
00:11:27.253 --> 00:11:28.822
Yeah. I was just trying to help.

244
00:11:28.888 --> 00:11:30.657
Like I said. she was good people.

245
00:11:30.724 --> 00:11:34.060
Got any idea why she
kept on running away?

246
00:11:34.127 --> 00:11:35.528
I think it was just too hard for her

247
00:11:35.595 --> 00:11:37.931
to still be in that world. you know?

248
00:11:37.964 --> 00:11:39.432
Seeing Craig coach other girls

249
00:11:39.566 --> 00:11:42.394
who still got to live the life
she thought she was gonna have.

250
00:11:42.494 --> 00:11:44.829
Plus he was crazy strict.

251
00:11:44.896 --> 00:11:46.606
And she stayed with you
again September of last year

252
00:11:46.673 --> 00:11:48.166
for a little while. too. right?

253
00:11:48.233 --> 00:11:50.276
Yeah. for about two weeks.

254
00:11:50.343 --> 00:11:52.145
But then we kind of had a fight

255
00:11:52.178 --> 00:11:54.481
and she left to go stay with
some guy she met in the city.

256
00:11:54.514 --> 00:11:56.616
You know the name of the guy
that she went to stay with?

257
00:11:56.683 --> 00:11:58.952
No. sorry.

258
00:11:58.985 --> 00:12:00.937
But I do know where they met.

259
00:12:03.490 --> 00:12:05.425
Have you seen this girl before?

260
00:12:07.018 --> 00:12:08.862
She used to hang out here a lot.

261
00:12:08.962 --> 00:12:11.948
Nah. Sorry. man. She
doesn't look familiar.

262
00:12:13.199 --> 00:12:14.567
You know this girl?

263
00:12:14.667 --> 00:12:17.804
Did she used to be blonde
and date a dude named Nips?

264
00:12:17.837 --> 00:12:19.105
I don't think so.

265
00:12:19.172 --> 00:12:21.374
Then nah. I don't know her.

266
00:12:23.176 --> 00:12:25.103
Damn. she's cute.

267
00:12:25.203 --> 00:12:27.038
Yeah. I would.

268
00:12:27.105 --> 00:12:29.340
That literally wasn't the question.

269
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:31.376
Oh. yeah. I know her.

270
00:12:31.443 --> 00:12:32.485
You do?

271
00:12:32.519 --> 00:12:33.820
I don't know her name or nothing.

272
00:12:33.853 --> 00:12:35.355
but she hangs out here all the time.

273
00:12:35.388 --> 00:12:36.923
I haven't seen her in a while. though.

274
00:12:37.023 --> 00:12:38.658
But her boyfriend. he
comes here all the time.

275
00:12:38.725 --> 00:12:40.160
Who's her boyfriend?

276
00:12:40.226 --> 00:12:43.054
I don't know his name either.
but he was here yesterday.

277
00:12:43.121 --> 00:12:45.098
White guy. long brown hair.

278
00:12:45.198 --> 00:12:46.357
He wears these crazy sneakers.

279
00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:49.569
They have. like. rainbow
and gold sparkles.

280
00:12:49.669 --> 00:12:50.795
All right. Thanks for your help.

281
00:12:50.862 --> 00:12:52.038
No doubt.

282
00:12:52.105 --> 00:12:53.306
Can't believe these kids are out here

283
00:12:53.373 --> 00:12:55.008
skateboarding in this weather.

284
00:12:55.041 --> 00:12:56.743
Well. that's dedication right there.

285
00:12:56.810 --> 00:12:59.679
Or mental illness.

286
00:12:59.712 --> 00:13:01.539
Wait. wait. wait.

287
00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:04.576
You gotta be kidding me.
Check out the sparkle shoes.

288
00:13:04.642 --> 00:13:07.687
Hey. Hey!

289
00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:10.582
NYPD. We need to talk
to you. Stay right there.

290
00:13:10.648 --> 00:13:12.709
I'm on him. Hey!

291
00:13:18.398 --> 00:13:20.934
Hey! NYPD!

292
00:13:35.715 --> 00:13:37.450
Theo. I'm north on Market.

293
00:13:37.517 --> 00:13:38.952
Hey!

294
00:13:42.113 --> 00:13:43.113
Hey!

295
00:13:49.929 --> 00:13:51.931
Vince. I lost him.

296
00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:52.998
He crossed. uh. Monroe.

297
00:13:53.066 --> 00:13:55.235
He's headed north through the alley.

298
00:13:55.301 --> 00:13:56.469
Copy that.

299
00:14:02.442 --> 00:14:03.977
I got him.

300
00:14:05.803 --> 00:14:06.980
Mechanics Alley.

301
00:14:18.558 --> 00:14:19.826
No. no. no. no!

302
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:35.675
- Hey. cop!
- I need an ambulance ASAP.

303
00:14:35.742 --> 00:14:37.569
Mechanics Alley between
Madison and Henry.

304
00:14:37.635 --> 00:14:40.280
10-53. H-I. Man down.

305
00:14:40.380 --> 00:14:42.615
What the hell?

306
00:14:42.682 --> 00:14:44.509
You just ran him down!

307
00:14:44.576 --> 00:14:45.743
Vince.

308
00:14:45.843 --> 00:14:47.854
Vince. what's going on? Are you okay?

309
00:14:47.921 --> 00:14:49.772
Hey. we'll have your
badge for this. cop!

310
00:14:59.649 --> 00:15:01.359
- Hey. Lou.
- Hey.

311
00:15:01.426 --> 00:15:02.660
You okay?

312
00:15:05.238 --> 00:15:06.573
Walk me through what happened.

313
00:15:06.639 --> 00:15:08.992
Got a lead on the suspect.
spotted him near the park.

314
00:15:09.025 --> 00:15:11.135
He ran. so I pursued him on foot.

315
00:15:11.202 --> 00:15:12.629
Vince was in the vehicle.

316
00:15:15.214 --> 00:15:17.350
I was closing in and

317
00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:19.377
a civilian just stepped into
the middle of the street.

318
00:15:19.477 --> 00:15:20.620
I mean. he... he came out of nowhere.

319
00:15:20.687 --> 00:15:22.021
Was your siren on?

320
00:15:22.088 --> 00:15:23.323
Yeah. of course it was.

321
00:15:23.389 --> 00:15:24.849
He just... you know. he
didn't... he didn't hear it.

322
00:15:24.949 --> 00:15:26.217
He had ear protection on.

323
00:15:26.317 --> 00:15:27.493
What's his status?

324
00:15:27.560 --> 00:15:28.628
He's in surgery now.

325
00:15:28.695 --> 00:15:30.230
Did the doctor say anything?

326
00:15:30.296 --> 00:15:31.497
No.

327
00:15:31.564 --> 00:15:33.533
Do we know anything about this guy?

328
00:15:33.633 --> 00:15:34.667
Derek Crosby.

329
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:36.069
Works for an electrical company.

330
00:15:36.169 --> 00:15:37.337
He was on the job.

331
00:15:37.403 --> 00:15:40.173
And he just walked into
the middle of the road?

332
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:42.909
The street was closed off to traffic.

333
00:15:42.976 --> 00:15:44.494
There were signs posted?

334
00:15:46.729 --> 00:15:48.581
Did you see them?

335
00:15:48.681 --> 00:15:49.999
Yeah.

336
00:15:54.687 --> 00:15:59.008
Uh. the suspect you were
chasing. was he armed?

337
00:16:01.552 --> 00:16:02.654
He had something in his hands

338
00:16:02.720 --> 00:16:04.222
that definitely could have been a gun.

339
00:16:09.419 --> 00:16:11.896
I... I wasn't sure. I
mean. could have been.

340
00:16:13.539 --> 00:16:15.375
Good.

341
00:16:15.441 --> 00:16:16.609
You followed protocol.

342
00:16:18.111 --> 00:16:19.345
Excuse me.

343
00:16:19.412 --> 00:16:20.705
Excuse me.

344
00:16:20.772 --> 00:16:22.148
My name is Sandra Crosby.

345
00:16:22.181 --> 00:16:24.550
I got a phone call that my
husband was hit by a car?

346
00:16:24.617 --> 00:16:26.886
- Yes. ma'am. He's here.
- He's currently in surgery.

347
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:29.047
Oh. my God. Is... is he okay?

348
00:16:29.113 --> 00:16:30.782
What... what's happening?

349
00:16:30.882 --> 00:16:32.884
Why don't you have a seat over here?

350
00:16:32.950 --> 00:16:34.377
I'll have the doctor
come and talk to you

351
00:16:34.444 --> 00:16:35.595
as soon as he's available.

352
00:16:35.662 --> 00:16:38.898
Would you like some
coffee or tea? Water?

353
00:16:44.203 --> 00:16:46.089
- You know what. Vince?
- I'm gonna handle the family.

354
00:16:46.122 --> 00:16:47.373
and I think you need to go home.

355
00:16:47.440 --> 00:16:48.608
I mean. I should...

356
00:16:48.708 --> 00:16:50.176
Yeah. but really. you shouldn't. right?

357
00:16:50.243 --> 00:16:52.637
You should just go home right now.

358
00:16:52.737 --> 00:16:54.747
She's right. It's been a lot. man.

359
00:16:54.814 --> 00:16:56.683
As soon as I'm done here.
I'll start an incident report.

360
00:16:56.749 --> 00:16:57.850
But right now. you need to go home.

361
00:16:57.884 --> 00:16:58.918
- Get some rest.
- Okay.

362
00:16:58.985 --> 00:17:00.820
All right. all right.

363
00:17:04.882 --> 00:17:06.150
Okay.

364
00:17:14.667 --> 00:17:16.536
Vince. Hey.

365
00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:19.639
Look. I'm fine. man. All right?

366
00:17:19.739 --> 00:17:21.574
I'm definitely not
going home to take a nap.

367
00:17:21.641 --> 00:17:23.601
I get that. Don't worry about it.

368
00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:25.278
We need to find Sparkle Shoes.

369
00:17:25.344 --> 00:17:26.813
I'll go through some security footage

370
00:17:26.879 --> 00:17:29.849
from the subway stations around
the alley where we lost him.

371
00:17:29.916 --> 00:17:32.744
If he took a train. maybe
we can track where he went.

372
00:17:32.777 --> 00:17:34.654
Yeah. I'll start pulling
the street cam from the park.

373
00:17:34.754 --> 00:17:36.122
Maybe we get a hit on facial rec.

374
00:17:36.189 --> 00:17:37.523
All right.

375
00:17:37.623 --> 00:17:38.623
Look. man. are you sure you're good?

376
00:17:38.649 --> 00:17:40.360
I'm fine. All right?

377
00:17:40.426 --> 00:17:42.278
Got a job to do. Let's go.

378
00:17:59.504 --> 00:18:01.180
You didn't touch your dinner.

379
00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:03.875
You should really eat something.

380
00:18:03.941 --> 00:18:05.051
I will.

381
00:18:06.686 --> 00:18:08.988
Any news from the hospital?

382
00:18:09.055 --> 00:18:14.427
Uh. Crosby is out of surgery.
but he's still in the ICU.

383
00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:18.064
Apparently he has significant
swelling in his brain.

384
00:18:20.057 --> 00:18:21.734
Doctors say it's 50/50.

385
00:18:24.504 --> 00:18:26.305
And how are you?

386
00:18:26.372 --> 00:18:28.574
I will be a lot better
when we catch this guy.

387
00:18:30.443 --> 00:18:32.712
Vince. I was thinking

388
00:18:32.979 --> 00:18:36.174
- maybe you should call...
- Look. I'm fine.

389
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:37.750
Okay? Really. I'm fine.

390
00:18:37.817 --> 00:18:39.043
Vince.

391
00:18:41.187 --> 00:18:42.588
All right. how about this?

392
00:18:42.688 --> 00:18:46.726
I will go to a meeting if I
feel like I really need one.

393
00:18:46.826 --> 00:18:48.920
Okay?

394
00:18:48.986 --> 00:18:49.986
Okay.

395
00:19:01.232 --> 00:19:02.525
I think that's him.

396
00:19:04.677 --> 00:19:05.878
Yeah. that's him.

397
00:19:05.978 --> 00:19:07.113
That's the man you were chasing?

398
00:19:07.213 --> 00:19:08.948
Yeah.

399
00:19:09.048 --> 00:19:10.316
From two days ago.

400
00:19:10.383 --> 00:19:11.884
What's he doing?

401
00:19:11.951 --> 00:19:14.704
Looks like he's recording
himself doing tricks.

402
00:19:14.770 --> 00:19:15.988
We saw him today.

403
00:19:16.022 --> 00:19:17.957
He was filming himself
with a selfie stick.

404
00:19:20.293 --> 00:19:23.062
Hey. Bridge.

405
00:19:23.129 --> 00:19:25.081
I was doing my homework. Dad. I swear.

406
00:19:25.114 --> 00:19:26.724
I was just looking up
how to spell a word.

407
00:19:26.757 --> 00:19:29.402
Yeah. sure you were.

408
00:19:29.468 --> 00:19:32.038
Look. I'm not here to bust you.

409
00:19:32.104 --> 00:19:34.632
Well. in that case. I
was actually on TikTok.

410
00:19:34.732 --> 00:19:35.942
- Sorry.
- Yeah. that's okay.

411
00:19:36.042 --> 00:19:37.410
That's actually what
I need your help with.

412
00:19:37.476 --> 00:19:39.445
Um. I'm trying to find somebody

413
00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:42.064
who I'm pretty sure posts videos online.

414
00:19:42.131 --> 00:19:44.217
but I don't know his name.

415
00:19:44.283 --> 00:19:47.478
Does this have to do
with what happened today?

416
00:19:47.545 --> 00:19:49.488
You eavesdropping on me and Mom?

417
00:19:49.522 --> 00:19:50.781
You're the one who said

418
00:19:50.882 --> 00:19:53.417
I should always be
aware of my surroundings.

419
00:19:53.451 --> 00:19:54.627
What do you know about the guy?

420
00:19:54.694 --> 00:19:56.729
Uh. not much. really.

421
00:19:56.796 --> 00:19:59.665
He... he makes videos of himself
skateboarding in the park.

422
00:19:59.765 --> 00:20:01.033
And he wears these sneakers

423
00:20:01.100 --> 00:20:02.835
with. like. glitter all over them.

424
00:20:02.935 --> 00:20:05.605
So I've been on Instagram and TikTok

425
00:20:05.671 --> 00:20:08.833
and I've tried every variation
of. you know. glitter shoes.

426
00:20:08.933 --> 00:20:09.976
uh. sparkle shoes...

427
00:20:10.042 --> 00:20:11.469
Let me guess. You got too many results?

428
00:20:11.569 --> 00:20:13.179
It's like everyone's
a content creator now?

429
00:20:13.279 --> 00:20:15.840
Really?

430
00:20:15.940 --> 00:20:17.583
Do you know what park he films in?

431
00:20:17.617 --> 00:20:19.769
Yeah. Lower East Side
Coleman Skate Park.

432
00:20:19.835 --> 00:20:20.953
If he tags his location.

433
00:20:21.020 --> 00:20:23.623
you might be able to find him that way.

434
00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:25.474
There's a map.

435
00:20:25.508 --> 00:20:27.393
All right.

436
00:20:27.460 --> 00:20:30.096
BennyHaps. AKA Benjamin Hoffman.

437
00:20:30.129 --> 00:20:31.781
Kid's got over 8 million followers.

438
00:20:31.847 --> 00:20:32.965
That's gotta be our guy.

439
00:20:33.065 --> 00:20:34.283
Come on. those are the same shoes.

440
00:20:34.350 --> 00:20:35.534
Oh. it's him.

441
00:20:35.601 --> 00:20:36.827
Techs pulled fingerprints
off the skateboard

442
00:20:36.928 --> 00:20:38.204
that he dropped at the park.

443
00:20:38.271 --> 00:20:40.464
It's a match to the partial
we found on the suitcase.

444
00:20:40.498 --> 00:20:41.607
This kid's 18 years old.

445
00:20:41.674 --> 00:20:43.367
He started blowing up when he was 14

446
00:20:43.467 --> 00:20:45.636
posting videos of himself
online skateboarding.

447
00:20:45.703 --> 00:20:46.812
doing stunts and stuff.

448
00:20:46.879 --> 00:20:48.047
Have you slept at all?

449
00:20:50.516 --> 00:20:53.060
In 2024. a girlfriend of his

450
00:20:53.061 --> 00:20:55.086
accused him of choking
her during an argument.

451
00:20:55.087 --> 00:20:56.505
She later dropped those charges.

452
00:20:56.539 --> 00:20:58.524
Clearly he has a history
of violence against women.

453
00:20:58.591 --> 00:20:59.725
Well. it gets better.

454
00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:01.661
According to this
"Forbes" article I found.

455
00:21:01.727 --> 00:21:03.663
"10 Content Creators to Watch."

456
00:21:03.729 --> 00:21:05.464
this kid made over 7 million last year.

457
00:21:05.531 --> 00:21:06.791
You're kidding me.

458
00:21:06.824 --> 00:21:08.059
Yeah. that's how he was
able to afford a condo

459
00:21:08.159 --> 00:21:10.069
in the building where
Lucia's body was found.

460
00:21:10.169 --> 00:21:11.654
But his name was not
on the list of owners

461
00:21:11.721 --> 00:21:13.030
the building's manager sent over.

462
00:21:13.130 --> 00:21:16.943
'Cause he sold the
condo... 4 1/2 months ago.

463
00:21:17.009 --> 00:21:18.411
Okay.

464
00:21:18.511 --> 00:21:19.670
Find him.

465
00:21:19.737 --> 00:21:20.737
Now.

466
00:21:25.918 --> 00:21:27.144
Someone lives here?

467
00:21:27.178 --> 00:21:29.080
I know. Pretty sick. right?

468
00:21:29.146 --> 00:21:30.848
Yo. Benny. there's some cops here.

469
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:33.584
They want to talk to you.

470
00:21:33.651 --> 00:21:35.027
Look. man. I didn't know...

471
00:21:35.094 --> 00:21:36.854
Yeah. Nowhere to run now. is there?

472
00:21:36.921 --> 00:21:38.197
Oh. whoa. whoa. whoa.

473
00:21:38.264 --> 00:21:39.924
Unless you want a lawsuit on your hands.

474
00:21:40.024 --> 00:21:41.759
I'd be a lot gentler. Officer.

475
00:21:41.826 --> 00:21:44.053
- Detective. Riley.
- Who are you?

476
00:21:44.086 --> 00:21:46.939
- I'm Cordelia Travers.
- I'm Mr. Hoffman's attorney.

477
00:21:49.008 --> 00:21:50.543
Don't say another word. Benjamin.

478
00:21:50.643 --> 00:21:51.869
- Fine by me.
- Ow.

479
00:21:51.936 --> 00:21:53.079
Turn around.

480
00:21:53.145 --> 00:21:54.897
Benjamin Hoffman...

481
00:21:54.930 --> 00:21:56.874
You're under arrest.

482
00:21:56.941 --> 00:21:59.076
Not a word.

483
00:22:04.282 --> 00:22:06.559
Yeah.

484
00:22:06.626 --> 00:22:08.227
Hoffman's not talking?

485
00:22:08.294 --> 00:22:09.662
Already lawyered up.

486
00:22:09.729 --> 00:22:13.024
- Cordelia Travers.
- He is not playing around.

487
00:22:13.057 --> 00:22:15.735
So what do we have?

488
00:22:15.801 --> 00:22:17.528
Hoffman's fingerprints match the partial

489
00:22:17.561 --> 00:22:19.063
that we found on the suitcase

490
00:22:19.130 --> 00:22:21.440
and his credit card statements
show that he purchased luggage

491
00:22:21.540 --> 00:22:22.967
that match the same make and model.

492
00:22:23.067 --> 00:22:26.345
Statements also show that
he purchased Lucia a phone.

493
00:22:26.379 --> 00:22:28.748
We found a slew of
messages between them.

494
00:22:28.814 --> 00:22:30.641
The texts establish that

495
00:22:30.741 --> 00:22:31.809
not only were they seeing each other.

496
00:22:31.876 --> 00:22:33.085
but she was staying with him

497
00:22:33.152 --> 00:22:35.755
in the condo building
where her body was found.

498
00:22:35.821 --> 00:22:39.583
All communication from her
stopped five months ago.

499
00:22:39.650 --> 00:22:40.760
So what's the theory?

500
00:22:40.826 --> 00:22:41.994
They had some kind of lover's quarrel.

501
00:22:42.061 --> 00:22:43.988
Hoffman kills her. puts
her in the suitcase.

502
00:22:44.088 --> 00:22:45.088
and then clears out?

503
00:22:45.131 --> 00:22:46.265
It's the most logical explanation.

504
00:22:46.365 --> 00:22:48.134
He's got a history of domestic violence.

505
00:22:48.234 --> 00:22:50.503
But it's unlikely that
will be admissible.

506
00:22:53.105 --> 00:22:55.900
We gotta charge him with
something or cut him loose.

507
00:22:55.966 --> 00:22:57.610
Charge him with reckless endangerment.

508
00:22:57.710 --> 00:23:00.946
Derek Crosby. the worker who
was injured during the pursuit.

509
00:23:01.013 --> 00:23:02.515
he's still in the ICU.

510
00:23:02.615 --> 00:23:03.949
Yeah. I don't think
that'll be necessary.

511
00:23:04.016 --> 00:23:07.244
But. um. let's charge
him with murder two.

512
00:23:07.311 --> 00:23:09.613
I can make this work.

513
00:23:14.593 --> 00:23:16.796
Vince.

514
00:23:16.862 --> 00:23:19.148
How'd it go with IAB?

515
00:23:19.181 --> 00:23:20.966
Fine. You know. I told
them what happened.

516
00:23:21.033 --> 00:23:22.868
Ruled it an accident.

517
00:23:22.968 --> 00:23:25.196
Good.

518
00:23:25.296 --> 00:23:26.839
If you want to talk about it. I'm...

519
00:23:26.906 --> 00:23:29.291
Yeah. yeah.

520
00:23:29.358 --> 00:23:31.502
I'm good. Thanks.

521
00:23:33.437 --> 00:23:35.548
Not a lot to say. you know?

522
00:23:40.703 --> 00:23:44.290
Introducing the prior
accusation of domestic abuse

523
00:23:44.356 --> 00:23:47.226
is more prejudicial than probative.

524
00:23:47.293 --> 00:23:49.795
The prosecution is grasping here.

525
00:23:49.862 --> 00:23:51.514
I wouldn't characterize it that way.

526
00:23:51.547 --> 00:23:52.932
And I'm not sure that's relevant.

527
00:23:52.965 --> 00:23:56.168
The assault charges against
my client were dropped.

528
00:23:56.235 --> 00:23:59.371
And quite frankly. Mr.
Price should know better.

529
00:23:59.472 --> 00:24:02.541
My colleague's indignation
notwithstanding.

530
00:24:02.641 --> 00:24:03.868
what I'm asking for. Your Honor.

531
00:24:03.968 --> 00:24:07.046
is to introduce testimony
from Amanda Waller.

532
00:24:07.113 --> 00:24:10.248
- The defendant's
ex-girlfriend? - That is correct.

533
00:24:10.249 --> 00:24:11.750
She will testify to an incident

534
00:24:11.851 --> 00:24:13.519
where Hoffman got
physically violent with her.

535
00:24:13.619 --> 00:24:15.488
The very definition of prior bad acts.

536
00:24:15.521 --> 00:24:16.521
You know. if you let me finish.

537
00:24:16.522 --> 00:24:17.522
Sure.

538
00:24:17.523 --> 00:24:18.591
He got physically violent with her

539
00:24:18.691 --> 00:24:20.192
and specifically choked her.

540
00:24:20.259 --> 00:24:23.129
Lucia Felasco's cause of
death was a broken neck.

541
00:24:23.195 --> 00:24:25.222
It speaks to a pattern of behavior

542
00:24:25.322 --> 00:24:27.900
and is therefore
admissible under Molineux.

543
00:24:27.967 --> 00:24:29.902
Choking someone and breaking their neck

544
00:24:29.969 --> 00:24:31.370
are not the same thing.

545
00:24:31.437 --> 00:24:32.930
Now who's grasping?

546
00:24:33.030 --> 00:24:35.107
Again. my client was
never formally charged.

547
00:24:35.207 --> 00:24:38.711
It's just one woman's claim.

548
00:24:38.778 --> 00:24:40.104
And the jury has the right to decide

549
00:24:40.171 --> 00:24:42.006
if they believe her or not.

550
00:24:42.072 --> 00:24:44.241
I'm siding with the prosecution here.

551
00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:51.073
He had his hand on my throat
and he was squeezing so hard.

552
00:24:51.106 --> 00:24:55.394
I screamed for him to stop.
but he just kept going.

553
00:24:55.461 --> 00:24:57.087
Did you believe he was gonna kill you?

554
00:24:57.188 --> 00:24:59.190
Objection. Calls for speculation.

555
00:24:59.256 --> 00:25:02.334
I will rephrase. Were
you scared for your life?

556
00:25:02.401 --> 00:25:03.769
100%.

557
00:25:03.869 --> 00:25:07.106
If someone hadn't stepped
in and pulled him off of me.

558
00:25:07.173 --> 00:25:08.399
he wouldn't have stopped.

559
00:25:08.465 --> 00:25:09.892
No further questions.

560
00:25:09.959 --> 00:25:12.611
Ms. Waller...

561
00:25:12.711 --> 00:25:15.915
you stated that during the fight.

562
00:25:15.981 --> 00:25:19.485
my client had his hand on your throat.

563
00:25:19.552 --> 00:25:20.653
Not both hands?

564
00:25:20.719 --> 00:25:21.779
No.

565
00:25:21.879 --> 00:25:23.055
Where was his other hand?

566
00:25:23.122 --> 00:25:24.782
Holding my wrist.

567
00:25:24.882 --> 00:25:27.718
Because he was trying to
stop you from pummeling him.

568
00:25:27.751 --> 00:25:29.887
In fact. multiple eyewitnesses

569
00:25:29.920 --> 00:25:32.398
report you instigated the altercation.

570
00:25:32.464 --> 00:25:35.993
You thought he was cheating
on you and you attacked him.

571
00:25:36.093 --> 00:25:38.470
They just said that because
they were all his friends.

572
00:25:38.537 --> 00:25:41.040
A man should never be
violent with a woman.

573
00:25:41.106 --> 00:25:44.168
He wasn't violent. he was
trying to protect himself.

574
00:25:44.235 --> 00:25:45.603
And you dropped the charges

575
00:25:45.636 --> 00:25:48.514
because you were the violent one.

576
00:25:48.581 --> 00:25:51.984
No. I just knew people like
you would take his side.

577
00:25:52.084 --> 00:25:55.145
This incident took
place at a house party.

578
00:25:55.246 --> 00:25:57.948
Are you saying you really
believed Mr. Hoffman

579
00:25:58.015 --> 00:26:00.359
was going to murder you in plain sight?

580
00:26:00.426 --> 00:26:01.919
Yes.

581
00:26:01.986 --> 00:26:03.020
You don't understand.

582
00:26:03.120 --> 00:26:04.922
Benny doesn't think things through.

583
00:26:04.955 --> 00:26:06.657
he just does stuff.

584
00:26:06.757 --> 00:26:08.667
And there are never consequences.

585
00:26:08.767 --> 00:26:11.604
And how old were you both
when this fight occurred?

586
00:26:11.670 --> 00:26:14.840
It was two years ago. so 16.

587
00:26:14.940 --> 00:26:16.575
Just a child.

588
00:26:16.642 --> 00:26:19.612
He already lived on his
own. He was an adult.

589
00:26:19.678 --> 00:26:21.380
Did you know Lucia Felasco?

590
00:26:21.447 --> 00:26:22.447
No.

591
00:26:22.448 --> 00:26:23.849
Were you present when she died?

592
00:26:23.949 --> 00:26:25.309
No.

593
00:26:25.376 --> 00:26:28.345
So you have no knowledge
of what happened to her

594
00:26:28.445 --> 00:26:31.156
or who's responsible for her death?

595
00:26:31.257 --> 00:26:34.860
- Not specifically. but I know how Benny...
- No further questions.

596
00:26:39.498 --> 00:26:43.335
Mr. Mason. you are the
defendant's assistant. correct?

597
00:26:43.402 --> 00:26:44.837
Uh. yeah.

598
00:26:44.937 --> 00:26:47.039
We didn't call it that. like.
formal or whatever. but yeah.

599
00:26:47.106 --> 00:26:48.440
he paid me to help him
out shooting content

600
00:26:48.507 --> 00:26:50.334
and running errands. stuff like that.

601
00:26:50.401 --> 00:26:53.612
Did he have you purchase
a phone for Lucia Felasco

602
00:26:53.646 --> 00:26:56.473
in late September of last
year with his credit card?

603
00:26:56.540 --> 00:26:58.617
He did. I thought it was pretty crazy.

604
00:26:58.684 --> 00:27:00.586
They only known each
other for. like. a week.

605
00:27:00.686 --> 00:27:02.379
and she was already living with him.

606
00:27:02.479 --> 00:27:04.248
Hmm. Did you have the
opportunity to spend much time

607
00:27:04.348 --> 00:27:05.841
with Lucia during that period?

608
00:27:05.908 --> 00:27:07.518
Yeah. we hung out a lot.

609
00:27:07.584 --> 00:27:08.794
She was cool.

610
00:27:08.861 --> 00:27:10.429
I am showing you what's
already been entered

611
00:27:10.529 --> 00:27:12.765
into evidence as Exhibit 4.

612
00:27:12.865 --> 00:27:15.768
This is the data from Lucia's phone.

613
00:27:15.868 --> 00:27:17.761
Records of every keystroke.

614
00:27:17.828 --> 00:27:19.238
every time it was unlocked.

615
00:27:19.305 --> 00:27:22.708
every text she sent. every
time she opened an app.

616
00:27:22.808 --> 00:27:26.729
Can you see that it shows that
she interacted with the device

617
00:27:26.762 --> 00:27:28.781
dozens of times a day.
just like you said?

618
00:27:28.881 --> 00:27:30.249
Yeah.

619
00:27:30.349 --> 00:27:32.409
And can you see that all
interaction with the phone

620
00:27:32.509 --> 00:27:38.424
ceased at 11:47 p.m. on the
evening of September 24th?

621
00:27:38.524 --> 00:27:39.917
Yes.

622
00:27:40.017 --> 00:27:44.380
From that point forward.
there is no activity at all.

623
00:27:44.446 --> 00:27:46.048
Do you have any idea why that is?

624
00:27:46.115 --> 00:27:47.191
No.

625
00:27:47.224 --> 00:27:48.434
Is it possible it's because

626
00:27:48.500 --> 00:27:49.693
that's the night she was killed?

627
00:27:49.760 --> 00:27:50.928
Objection!

628
00:27:51.028 --> 00:27:53.297
Witness has no way of knowing this

629
00:27:53.364 --> 00:27:55.074
and already stated as much.

630
00:27:55.140 --> 00:27:56.400
Sustained.

631
00:27:56.467 --> 00:27:58.736
Mr. Mason. did you see Benjamin Hoffman

632
00:27:58.769 --> 00:27:59.978
on the night of September 24th?

633
00:28:00.045 --> 00:28:02.539
Yeah. I went over to
his place around 9:00

634
00:28:02.573 --> 00:28:04.116
and hung out for. like. half an hour.

635
00:28:04.216 --> 00:28:06.751
- Was Lucia Felasco there?
- Yes.

636
00:28:06.752 --> 00:28:09.855
When you left around 9:30.

637
00:28:09.922 --> 00:28:12.324
were the defendant and Ms.
Felasco alone in the apartment?

638
00:28:12.391 --> 00:28:13.459
Yes.

639
00:28:13.460 --> 00:28:17.162
Did you ever see her again after that?

640
00:28:17.229 --> 00:28:18.731
No.

641
00:28:18.797 --> 00:28:21.558
She was never seen or heard
from by anyone after that.

642
00:28:21.592 --> 00:28:23.894
Never touched her phone again.

643
00:28:23.927 --> 00:28:26.271
Did you receive a call from Mr. Hoffman

644
00:28:26.338 --> 00:28:28.674
the next day on September 25th?

645
00:28:28.774 --> 00:28:30.042
Yeah.

646
00:28:30.109 --> 00:28:31.910
He asked me to run an errand for him.

647
00:28:31.944 --> 00:28:33.637
He sent me to buy him a suitcase.

648
00:28:35.147 --> 00:28:37.983
Is this the suitcase you
purchased on Mr. Hoffman's behalf?

649
00:28:38.050 --> 00:28:39.585
It looks like it. yeah.

650
00:28:39.618 --> 00:28:40.853
It's the suitcase that was found

651
00:28:40.919 --> 00:28:43.105
with the defendant's
fingerprint on it and...

652
00:28:44.615 --> 00:28:48.018
With Lucia Felasco's
dead body stuffed inside.

653
00:28:48.085 --> 00:28:49.695
Thank you. Nothing further.

654
00:28:52.498 --> 00:28:55.150
Did my client ever explain to you

655
00:28:55.184 --> 00:28:57.503
why Ms. Felasco was no longer
living in his apartment?

656
00:28:57.569 --> 00:29:00.839
Uh. yeah. he said that she
broke up with him and took off.

657
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:02.791
Something she had a history of doing.

658
00:29:02.858 --> 00:29:04.743
So is it possible

659
00:29:04.810 --> 00:29:07.271
that the reason she
stopped using her phone

660
00:29:07.304 --> 00:29:08.680
was that she didn't bring it with her

661
00:29:08.781 --> 00:29:11.475
because she knew that Mr.
Hoffman was paying for it?

662
00:29:11.542 --> 00:29:12.885
Sure. That makes sense.

663
00:29:12.985 --> 00:29:14.670
And isn't it also possible

664
00:29:14.703 --> 00:29:17.781
that he put the luggage
that you purchased

665
00:29:17.815 --> 00:29:19.817
in his apartment storage unit

666
00:29:19.883 --> 00:29:20.959
in the basement of his building.

667
00:29:20.993 --> 00:29:22.761
a basement it has been established

668
00:29:22.828 --> 00:29:24.888
anyone could have access to?

669
00:29:24.988 --> 00:29:26.290
I guess so. yeah.

670
00:29:26.356 --> 00:29:29.835
And lastly. in your time
working for my client.

671
00:29:29.902 --> 00:29:34.898
did you ever see him behave
violently toward Ms. Felasco.

672
00:29:34.965 --> 00:29:37.409
or anyone. for that matter?

673
00:29:38.977 --> 00:29:41.246
No.

674
00:29:41.346 --> 00:29:43.907
He was always pretty chill.

675
00:29:43.974 --> 00:29:45.150
Indeed.

676
00:29:45.217 --> 00:29:46.585
Thank you.

677
00:29:46.618 --> 00:29:47.920
Nothing further.

678
00:29:49.688 --> 00:29:51.248
We'll end there for today.

679
00:29:51.315 --> 00:29:52.983
The trial will resume
tomorrow at 9:00 a.m.

680
00:29:53.016 --> 00:29:54.718
Court is adjourned.

681
00:30:05.587 --> 00:30:07.106
Price.

682
00:30:07.172 --> 00:30:08.499
- Hold up.
- Oh. Cordelia.

683
00:30:08.565 --> 00:30:09.867
What... Let me guess.

684
00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:11.435
Uh. you want to discuss a deal?

685
00:30:11.535 --> 00:30:12.711
Oh. I forgot how brilliant you are.

686
00:30:12.778 --> 00:30:13.846
Not interested.

687
00:30:13.912 --> 00:30:15.606
Uh. you should be.

688
00:30:15.672 --> 00:30:17.015
And why is that?

689
00:30:17.049 --> 00:30:20.744
Because he's willing to tell
you what really happened.

690
00:30:27.893 --> 00:30:33.098
I really cared about
Lucia. She was funny. sweet.

691
00:30:33.165 --> 00:30:34.900
Her life had been tough. you know?

692
00:30:34.967 --> 00:30:37.035
I understood. I...

693
00:30:37.136 --> 00:30:40.005
I started making real money
as an influencer when I was 15.

694
00:30:40.105 --> 00:30:41.573
but my parents were stealing from me.

695
00:30:41.640 --> 00:30:44.610
My... my dad lost a
lot of that gambling.

696
00:30:44.676 --> 00:30:46.979
So I took them to
court. I got emancipated.

697
00:30:47.045 --> 00:30:52.209
We both have basically
been alone since we were 15.

698
00:30:52.309 --> 00:30:54.603
Right. you were two lonely
kids adrift in the world

699
00:30:54.636 --> 00:30:55.636
till you found each other.

700
00:30:55.637 --> 00:30:57.656
So what made you kill her?

701
00:30:57.723 --> 00:31:01.026
I would never hurt Lucia or anyone else.

702
00:31:01.093 --> 00:31:02.945
Oh. okay. So you are
just wasting our time.

703
00:31:02.978 --> 00:31:06.164
Would you let him speak?

704
00:31:06.231 --> 00:31:08.667
Why don't you just
tell us what happened?

705
00:31:10.469 --> 00:31:12.629
Go ahead. They can't
use any of this in court.

706
00:31:16.808 --> 00:31:20.679
I didn't kill Lucia. but I
was there when it happened.

707
00:31:20.746 --> 00:31:23.265
- We were partying that night...
- Meaning you were doing drugs.

708
00:31:26.151 --> 00:31:27.686
Cocaine.

709
00:31:27.753 --> 00:31:32.482
That's why Cory stopped by.
He was making a delivery.

710
00:31:32.516 --> 00:31:35.260
We got high and Lucia started showing me

711
00:31:35.360 --> 00:31:38.664
some of her old gymnastic
moves on my trampoline.

712
00:31:38.697 --> 00:31:40.532
It was all good vibes.

713
00:31:40.599 --> 00:31:42.618
We were laughing. And then...

714
00:31:44.903 --> 00:31:47.206
She did a... did a backflip

715
00:31:47.306 --> 00:31:49.074
and she was too close to the edge.

716
00:31:49.174 --> 00:31:52.344
so she hit the side

717
00:31:52.411 --> 00:31:56.673
and she landed on the floor on her head.

718
00:31:56.707 --> 00:32:00.168
And the sound was just...

719
00:32:04.723 --> 00:32:08.385
Um...

720
00:32:08.452 --> 00:32:13.232
It... it... it was an accident.

721
00:32:16.393 --> 00:32:20.339
If it was just an accident.
then why didn't you call 911?

722
00:32:20.405 --> 00:32:24.676
I... um. I panicked. I...

723
00:32:24.810 --> 00:32:26.612
There were drugs everywhere! I...

724
00:32:26.678 --> 00:32:28.580
and even though she's only
ten months younger than me.

725
00:32:28.680 --> 00:32:30.015
she's still technically underage.

726
00:32:30.048 --> 00:32:33.051
So you thought that
putting her in a suitcase

727
00:32:33.118 --> 00:32:35.687
and leaving her there would
get you in less trouble?

728
00:32:35.787 --> 00:32:38.690
I was high! I wasn't thinking clearly.

729
00:32:38.724 --> 00:32:41.760
I just wanted to run away and
never think about it again.

730
00:32:44.529 --> 00:32:46.923
I know what I did was wrong.

731
00:32:46.990 --> 00:32:48.700
I know.

732
00:32:48.734 --> 00:32:51.536
And I'm... I'm sorry.

733
00:32:51.670 --> 00:32:53.238
I just...

734
00:32:53.305 --> 00:32:55.899
I just felt like the rest of
my life would have been ruined.

735
00:33:00.412 --> 00:33:01.713
Why didn't you tell us that

736
00:33:01.847 --> 00:33:04.441
when he was charged with murder?

737
00:33:04.508 --> 00:33:07.077
He just told me the truth two days ago.

738
00:33:08.845 --> 00:33:11.256
And tell me. Mr. Hoffman...

739
00:33:11.323 --> 00:33:15.327
Mr. Hoffman. do you have any
evidence to back up this story?

740
00:33:15.394 --> 00:33:18.063
Uh. no.

741
00:33:18.130 --> 00:33:22.067
But I swear it was an accident.

742
00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:23.669
He's willing to plead guilty

743
00:33:23.769 --> 00:33:26.405
to the concealment of a human corpse.

744
00:33:26.438 --> 00:33:28.140
That's the proper charge here.

745
00:33:32.294 --> 00:33:34.062
Offer declined.

746
00:33:39.810 --> 00:33:42.120
That's okay.

747
00:33:42.187 --> 00:33:46.692
I... I just... I wanted
to tell the truth.

748
00:33:46.792 --> 00:33:48.326
It was an accident.

749
00:33:52.823 --> 00:33:54.199
Call Riley.

750
00:33:54.299 --> 00:33:56.335
Tell him I need him to testify
first thing in the morning

751
00:33:56.435 --> 00:34:00.005
about Hoffman fleeing when
they tried to question him.

752
00:34:00.072 --> 00:34:02.941
It will establish Hoffman's
consciousness of guilt.

753
00:34:02.974 --> 00:34:04.209
Will do.

754
00:34:04.276 --> 00:34:06.294
But Nolan...

755
00:34:06.328 --> 00:34:09.973
Are you sure we shouldn't
consider accepting the plea?

756
00:34:10.006 --> 00:34:13.418
Just take his word for it
that it was an accident?

757
00:34:13.518 --> 00:34:14.786
Well. we could call the assistant again.

758
00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:16.580
see if he was actually there that night

759
00:34:16.680 --> 00:34:18.890
to deliver the cocaine.

760
00:34:18.957 --> 00:34:20.492
Yeah.

761
00:34:20.525 --> 00:34:22.252
That still wouldn't prove that
Hoffman's telling the truth

762
00:34:22.319 --> 00:34:23.462
about the rest of it.

763
00:34:23.495 --> 00:34:24.496
Mm. I don't know.

764
00:34:24.563 --> 00:34:25.997
That scenario he laid out

765
00:34:26.031 --> 00:34:28.316
could very well result
in a C1 cervical fracture.

766
00:34:28.350 --> 00:34:29.434
It's plausible.

767
00:34:29.534 --> 00:34:31.503
Okay. but he... he
can't prove any of it.

768
00:34:31.570 --> 00:34:33.472
Well. we can't prove he's lying either.

769
00:34:33.505 --> 00:34:34.973
And if he's telling the truth.

770
00:34:35.040 --> 00:34:38.910
then the appropriate sentence
is 5 years. not 25 to life.

771
00:34:38.977 --> 00:34:42.080
His actions don't make any sense

772
00:34:42.180 --> 00:34:43.682
in the context of an accident.

773
00:34:43.749 --> 00:34:47.586
He shoved her dead body into
a suitcase and left her to rot.

774
00:34:47.686 --> 00:34:50.222
That is... is not the behavior
of someone who is innocent.

775
00:34:50.288 --> 00:34:51.990
Well. sometimes people
behave irrationally

776
00:34:52.023 --> 00:34:55.018
when something crazy happens.

777
00:34:55.051 --> 00:34:58.663
The defense is welcome to present
their version of events to the jury.

778
00:34:58.697 --> 00:35:00.724
I would love to see how
they react to the news

779
00:35:00.791 --> 00:35:03.960
that Hoffman has been lying
to them this entire time.

780
00:35:04.027 --> 00:35:05.070
Call Riley.

781
00:35:12.144 --> 00:35:15.906
Mr. Price. are you ready
to call your next witness?

782
00:35:15.972 --> 00:35:17.416
Uh...

783
00:35:19.976 --> 00:35:21.711
Just one moment. Your Honor.

784
00:35:26.091 --> 00:35:27.717
Mr. Price.

785
00:35:30.061 --> 00:35:33.698
Uh. Your Honor. it seems we
are having some difficulty

786
00:35:33.832 --> 00:35:35.392
locating our next witness.

787
00:35:35.425 --> 00:35:37.369
We request a brief continuance
while we look into the matter.

788
00:35:37.502 --> 00:35:41.072
Uh. with all due
respect. not our problem.

789
00:35:41.106 --> 00:35:42.941
Defense requests we move forward.

790
00:35:45.477 --> 00:35:47.404
I'll give you 24 hours.

791
00:35:50.348 --> 00:35:52.117
Okay. thanks.

792
00:35:54.052 --> 00:35:56.446
That was Brady. She
spoke with Riley's wife.

793
00:35:56.513 --> 00:35:57.914
She can't get ahold of him either.

794
00:35:57.948 --> 00:36:00.725
He's not answering anyone's phone calls.

795
00:36:00.859 --> 00:36:02.961
Okay.

796
00:36:03.028 --> 00:36:04.763
Um...

797
00:36:04.830 --> 00:36:08.091
well. let's start
calling around hospitals.

798
00:36:08.124 --> 00:36:11.294
see if anyone has been admitted
who matches his description.

799
00:36:11.361 --> 00:36:13.096
Hey. hey. Man. I'm sorry.

800
00:36:13.129 --> 00:36:14.906
- Vince.
- I'm sorry. All right?

801
00:36:14.940 --> 00:36:16.174
I... I was a no-show.

802
00:36:16.241 --> 00:36:19.277
We've been looking for
you. We were worried.

803
00:36:19.344 --> 00:36:21.146
Hey. what's going on?

804
00:36:21.213 --> 00:36:23.415
Uh...

805
00:36:23.548 --> 00:36:24.683
Are you okay?

806
00:36:24.749 --> 00:36:27.435
Uh. Derek Crosby was. um.

807
00:36:27.469 --> 00:36:29.379
declared brain dead this morning

808
00:36:29.479 --> 00:36:31.323
and his family took
him off life support.

809
00:36:33.617 --> 00:36:35.927
Why don't we go in my office?

810
00:36:36.061 --> 00:36:37.662
Come on.

811
00:36:39.464 --> 00:36:42.334
Uh. I will get us some coffee.

812
00:36:42.400 --> 00:36:46.254
Call Brady and let her
know he's been found.

813
00:36:50.842 --> 00:36:54.112
Here. have some of this.

814
00:36:54.145 --> 00:36:56.139
Crosby's death is my fault.

815
00:36:56.172 --> 00:36:57.949
- No. it was an accident.
- No.

816
00:36:57.983 --> 00:36:59.242
No. I was reckless.

817
00:36:59.342 --> 00:37:00.969
Vince. have you been drinking?

818
00:37:01.002 --> 00:37:02.320
What difference does that make?

819
00:37:02.387 --> 00:37:04.247
Is that a yes?

820
00:37:04.347 --> 00:37:05.524
I saw the orange signs.

821
00:37:05.590 --> 00:37:07.125
I should have been more careful.

822
00:37:07.158 --> 00:37:08.727
You were pursuing a murder suspect.

823
00:37:08.793 --> 00:37:09.986
He stepped in front of your vehicle.

824
00:37:10.020 --> 00:37:12.989
- There's nothing...
- I knew he wasn't armed!

825
00:37:13.023 --> 00:37:15.233
Hoffman. I had no reason
to think that he had a gun.

826
00:37:15.333 --> 00:37:17.903
No. but you said that
you saw in his hand...

827
00:37:17.969 --> 00:37:20.931
I lied.

828
00:37:20.997 --> 00:37:22.173
Make my actions seem justified.

829
00:37:22.207 --> 00:37:23.542
Hey. Vince. you need to be careful.

830
00:37:23.608 --> 00:37:26.745
I just... I'm scared for
my career and my whole life.

831
00:37:26.811 --> 00:37:29.381
I... I'm not the person you
should be saying this to.

832
00:37:29.447 --> 00:37:33.685
I am a prosecutor. not a priest.

833
00:37:33.752 --> 00:37:37.822
You're exactly the person
I need to say this to.

834
00:37:37.856 --> 00:37:40.784
I want to... I want to tell the truth.

835
00:37:40.884 --> 00:37:42.018
I screwed up.

836
00:37:42.052 --> 00:37:43.428
- And now...
- Vince. stop talking.

837
00:37:53.939 --> 00:37:58.443
You didn't want this to happen.

838
00:37:58.510 --> 00:38:00.679
And you were doing your job.

839
00:38:00.812 --> 00:38:03.164
And... and...

840
00:38:05.550 --> 00:38:07.310
Accidents happen.

841
00:38:07.410 --> 00:38:10.021
It's not right. it's not fair.

842
00:38:10.088 --> 00:38:11.756
It's just the way it is.

843
00:38:16.962 --> 00:38:22.017
But you can't let one accident
destroy the rest of your life.

844
00:38:33.111 --> 00:38:35.046
Is there someone I can call? Your wife?

845
00:38:35.113 --> 00:38:36.172
- No.
- A sponsor?

846
00:38:36.272 --> 00:38:39.067
No. no. no. I'm good.

847
00:38:39.100 --> 00:38:40.418
Hey.

848
00:38:40.452 --> 00:38:43.154
Look. I'm good. I'm
good. I'm good. I'm good.

849
00:38:51.696 --> 00:38:54.457
How's he doing?

850
00:38:54.524 --> 00:38:57.802
Uh. yeah. he's having a hard time.

851
00:38:57.869 --> 00:39:01.272
I'm just gonna go make
sure he gets home all right.

852
00:39:01.306 --> 00:39:04.242
Um...

853
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:05.944
Call Cory Mason.

854
00:39:06.011 --> 00:39:09.981
Let's... let's see if he
backs up Hoffman's claims.

855
00:39:18.314 --> 00:39:21.159
So what's this about?

856
00:39:21.226 --> 00:39:23.595
Well. your client's assistant confirmed

857
00:39:23.662 --> 00:39:26.865
that he was at the apartment
that night to deliver cocaine.

858
00:39:26.931 --> 00:39:29.434
We are willing to drop
the murder two charge

859
00:39:29.467 --> 00:39:31.169
in exchange for him pleading guilty

860
00:39:31.236 --> 00:39:32.704
to concealment of a human corpse.

861
00:39:32.804 --> 00:39:35.799
And reckless endangerment.

862
00:39:35.832 --> 00:39:38.793
And assuming his version
of events is true.

863
00:39:38.827 --> 00:39:40.645
he purchased and
provided Lucia with drugs

864
00:39:40.712 --> 00:39:42.680
which were directly causal to her death.

865
00:39:42.781 --> 00:39:44.582
He'll be looking at 6 to 8 years

866
00:39:44.682 --> 00:39:46.518
instead of 25 to life.

867
00:39:51.656 --> 00:39:52.791
We've got a deal.

868
00:39:52.824 --> 00:39:54.317
We'll draw up the agreement.

869
00:39:56.519 --> 00:40:00.782
So Counselor. what caused
you to reverse course?

870
00:40:03.835 --> 00:40:06.404
Thought there was a chance
the jury might believe him.

871
00:40:06.504 --> 00:40:08.990
Wow. Not a change of heart? Pfft.

872
00:40:09.023 --> 00:40:10.023
That's a shame.

873
00:40:10.041 --> 00:40:12.143
I'll buy you a drink. Come on.

874
00:40:14.946 --> 00:40:19.709
It's been two months since I last drank.

875
00:40:19.776 --> 00:40:24.672
Prior to that. I'd almost
made it to the one-year mark.

876
00:40:24.706 --> 00:40:29.494
But I...

877
00:40:29.527 --> 00:40:32.055
had a few bad days.

878
00:40:32.122 --> 00:40:35.467
And I...

879
00:40:35.533 --> 00:40:36.860
I slipped.

880
00:40:39.471 --> 00:40:43.908
And it's hard.

881
00:40:44.008 --> 00:40:49.539
But yesterday was easier than today.

882
00:40:49.572 --> 00:40:53.518
So there's that.

883
00:40:53.551 --> 00:40:58.039
I know I just have to get up every day

884
00:40:58.072 --> 00:40:59.716
and keep going.

885
00:41:01.718 --> 00:41:03.344
And I will.

886
00:41:05.530 --> 00:41:07.098
I will.

887
